sharedPost.text: Video: "I heard a statement at Kololo during the #SONA2024 which scared me to the bone. President Museveni said that if he goes hard on corruption, who is he going to work with? Corruption is a cancer. If you look at the treatment of cancer it is severe. It must be removed and everywhere it has got its tentacles in", UPC President Hon. Jimmy Akena  while on NextRadio Big Talk on June 8, 2024

The NRM National Treasurer Amb. Barbara Nekesa has castigated some media reports that allege that the ruling party is planning to sell party flags to aspiring candidates during primary elections from presidential to village positions.

On Tuesday 15th April, the NRM Secretary General, Rt. Hon. Richard Todwong issued a list of nomination fees to aspirants intending to contest at every position. The guidelines stipulate that the presidential flagbearer aspirants will pay 20 million, 3 million for Members of Parliament and 1.5 Million for those interested in the position of the Lord Mayor. The LCV chairperson, district councillor and division mayor aspirants will part ways with 1 million each.  

In her response yesterday during an induction meeting with NRM District Election Officers at party election offices at plot 13, Kyadondo, Amb. Nekesa said, “We are not selling flags. I don't know what some media houses intend to achieve in all this, because this is the highest level of misinformation.”

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/we-are-not-selling-nrm-flags-ambnekesa-responds-media-reports

text:
President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni has emphasized the urgent need to prioritize household income generation, describing it as a cornerstone of national development.

During a leaders meeting held at Mwanzi Parish, Mirembe Maria Catholic Parish in Kasanda District yesterday, President Museveni reminded Ugandans that, just as spiritual teachings guide priorities, “Seek first the Kingdom of God and all these things shall be added unto you”, the nation must apply the same principle by seeking household income first.

The meeting was part of the ongoing Presidential performance assessment tour on wealth creation and Parish Development Model (PDM) in Greater Mubende.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/blog/president-museveni-emphasizes-focus-household-income-development

text:
The NRM District Election Officers (Registrars) have been urged to uphold integrity and high moral standards as they conduct the upcoming structure and primary elections. The electoral roadmap 2025-26 was released yesterday beginning with the nomination for structure elections at the village level and LC1 chairpersons.

In a meeting presided by the NRM Secretary General Rt. Hon.Richard Todwong, the registrars from across the country were cautioned against being manipulated by aspirants of various elective seats through gifts or monetary reward.

“The integrity of NRM leadership will be tested by your works in the exercise we are yet to undertake. Don’t be compromised. The stake is high. The interests are compounded. You are going to be accused either wrongly or correctly. Stand for the right things. I rather you are accused by members for standing on the side of truth,” Todwong said.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/uphold-integrity-during-primary-elections-todwong-tells-nrm-district-election-officers

UPDATE: Former students, alumni, and staff of Mbarara University of Science and Technology (MUST), under the MUST Convocation, are fundraising UGX 530 million to build an iconic gate and perimeter wall at the town campus, under the theme "Building My Alma Mater."

MUST Chancellor Prof. Charles Mark Olwenyi praised the initiative, calling it a meaningful investment in safety, pride, and future generations of the university.

text:
President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni continues to express frustration about those failing to implement the government policy of free education across the country, calling upon leaders at all levels to ensure that the program is fully implemented.

“I don’t want to use force on this matter. Discuss the issue of free education in government schools, including the technical schools. If we need to add more money to the government schools, we shall do it,” President Museveni said.

The President made the remarks today, while commissioning the Greater Mubende Presidential Zonal Skilling Hub in Kibuye-Vuga Village, Kitenga Sub County, Mubende District.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/blog/i-dont-want-use-force-matter-president-museveni-reiterates-call-free-education

text:
President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni yesterday visited Kyankwanzi District as part of his ongoing assessment of the Parish Development Model (PDM), Uganda’s flagship initiative aimed at eradicating household poverty through commercial agriculture and financial inclusion.

During his visit to Bugomolwa Parish in Nkandwa Sub-county, President Museveni met Mr. Matovu Patrick, a PDM beneficiary who has successfully utilized the program’s support to improve his family’s livelihood.

Mr. Matovu received UGX 980,000 through the PDM, which he invested in purchasing 40 chicks at UGX 15,000 each, totaling UGX 600,000. He allocated UGX 100,000 for feed and an additional UGX 100,000 for iron sheets to construct a shelter. After six months, he sold 10 chickens at UGX 45,000 each, earning UGX 450,000. He supplemented this with UGX 400,000 from coffee sales to purchase a bull. Currently, Mr. Matovu earns UGX 40,000 per month from egg sales, selling one tray weekly at UGX 10,000. He utilizes cow dung and chicken droppings as fertilizers for his coffee and banana plantations, enhancing crop quality and yield.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/blog/president-museveni-announces-plan-increase-pdm-funding

text:
HAPPENING NOW: Members of the NRM Secretariat top leadership, led by the Secretary General, Rt Hon. Richard Todwong, are meeting with party electoral district registrars in preparation for the rollout of the election activities. 

SG Todwong yesterday launched the party's political and elections roadmap 2025-26 for the primary and structure elections.

text:
Standing with Chadema and Hon. Tundu Lissu

We at FDC stand in full solidarity with our comrades in Tanzania's Chadema Party and Hon. Tundu Lissu during these trying times.

It's deeply concerning to see Chadema barred from participating in the upcoming October elections and their Presidential Flagbearer Hon. Tundu Lissu charged with treason-a man who has already endured immense adversity for his commitment to democracy.

In 2017, Hon. Lissu survived an assassination attempt where he was shot 16 times near his home in Dodoma. 

Now, as he faces treason charges for advocating electoral reforms, we recognize the pattern of political repression aimed at silencing opposition voices in Tanzania

To Hon. Lissu and Chadema: your resilience inspires us. Your fight for justice and democracy is not in vain. 

We stand with you in solidarity, committed to the shared goal of a free and democratic Africa.

text:
President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni has expressed gratitude to the Catholic Church for their active role in combating poverty and promoting socio-economic development.

According to the President, it is important to integrate spiritual guidance with practical efforts to uplift communities economically.

“I'm happy to see that the priest is walking in the footsteps of Jesus Christ, whose mission had four dimensions: to preach the gospel, heal the sick, feed the hungry, and himself worked in the carpentry. I have seen the coffee, cows, and pigs, and also helped our people. I’m also going to help them,” H.E. Museveni said.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/blog/president-museveni-hails-catholic-church-fighting-poverty

text:
‎The NRM Secretary-General, Rt Hon. Richard Todwong today Tuesday morning held talks with the Ambassador of The Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia to Uganda, Her Excellency Etsegenet Bezabih Yimenu. The cordial meeting took place at NRM headquarters at Plot 10, Kyadondo Road.

‎The bilateral discussions between SG Todwong and H.E Bezabih Yimenu highlighted the commitment of both parties to continue collaborating on various fronts, including politics, trade, and cultural exchange between Uganda and Ethiopia.

‎"We cherish our treasured historical ties and mutual relations between the people of Ethiopia and Uganda," Mr Todwong said.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/ethiopia-ambassador-he-yimenu-pays-courtesy-call-nrms-todwong

text:
If you are a leader,  you are in an advantage position,  If you are at an advantaged position, allow others to reach and attain their small goals through your assistance. 

Be a pillar, not an obstacle. I remind myself of this everyday. When you have power, know that the favours you get, the courtesies you receive, the respect accorded you, none is really serving you. 

They are actually serving the power in you. The day power leaves you, is the day all privileges disappear. Learn to be humble and simple. 

NOTE THAT WHEN SOMEONE HAS BEEN GIVEN MUCH, MUCH WILL BE REQUIRED IN RETURN; AND WHEN SOMEONE HAS BEEN ENTRUSTED WITH MUCH, EVEN MORE WILL BE REQUIRED.

text:
‎The NRM political and electoral roadmap 2025-26 has today been released by the Secretary-General, Rt. Hon. Richard Todwong, flanked by members of the NRM Secretariat Top leadership. 
‎
‎In a press conference held today, the Secretary-General said the program will begin next week on April 24th with the expression of interest and nomination for party structure elections at the village level and LC1 Chairperson. 

He described the event as a very important milestone for the party and called on Party members to be very observant of the dates proposed for all the Party activities.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/nrm-releases-roadmap-primary-and-structure-elections

text:
A group of over 500 patriotic youth in Gulu City say they are ready to campaign for the NRM and President Museveni in the coming elections due to his endeavours of uplifting the population out of poverty. 

In a meeting held yesterday by the NRM Secretary General, Rt Hon. Richard Todwong, in Gulu city, the enthusiastic group pledged utmost loyalty to President Museveni for empowerment policies like the Parish Development Model and Emyooga to boost incomes. 

"We intend to advance the NRM agenda of socio-economic transformation through the 'musevenomics' leadership approach, which blends foresight, regional integration, peaceful coexistence, stability and pragmatic development."

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/gulu-youth-cadres-pledge-campaign-president-museveni

text:
The NRM Deputy Secretary General, Rt. Hon. Namayanja Rose Nsereko has rallied the people of Mubende to support President Museveni, noting that the NRM government is committed to resolving people's challenges. 
‎
‎Namayanja made the call yesterday while speaking at the 5th Buganda for Museveni rally in Kasana Playground, Mubende Municipality. She explained that the engagement is meant to raise awareness among citizens about the NRM government's achievements and plans.
‎
‎"The rallies we began throughout Buganda are meant to help us spread the NRM government gospel to the population in terms of its achievements. As NRM, we know where we have come from, where we are, and where we are going,” Namayanja said.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/nrm-committed-resolve-peoples-challenges-namayanja-tells-mubende-residents

text:
Russia intercepts 71 Ukrainian drones in a wide overnight assault, while Gaza remains littered with unexploded bombs as Israeli airstrikes resume. 

Spanish police uncover an illegal underground shooting range linked to organized crime hidden three floors below a Granada home, with weapons and cash seized.

A meeting involving key government entities and stakeholders discussed potential challenges in Uganda-Dubai relations. 

The discussions also focused on streamlining operations of the Uganda Business Center in Dubai, which was launched to help Ugandan entrepreneurs explore business opportunities and promote tourism between the two countries.

NRM Party leadership in Gulu has intensified preparations for the upcoming internal structure elections.

text: It’s raining goals at the Emirates!

APAA LAND WRANGLES

The continued clashes between the Madi and Acholi communities over the Apaa land continue to claim more lives and deepen the rift between our people.

It is time for the elders and leaders from both sides to rise above the conflict and come together to seek a lasting solution. 

Whether the land belongs to the Acholi or the Madi, we are all Ugandans we must learn to coexist peacefully because we are one Uganda, one People.

text:
A new Makerere University Walter Reed Project and Ministry of Health study has revealed gaps in emergency preparedness in public health labs within the central region. 

While biosafety efforts exist, many labs especially rural Health Center IIIs lack emergency plans, biosecurity infrastructure, and basic tools like first aid kits, putting staff and communities at serious risk.

#NBSLiveAt1 #NBSUpdates

text:
The Kyangwali Refugee Settlement administration has raised concern over the growing influx of refugees from the Democratic Republic of Congo, with many currently stranded at the overcrowded Kagoma Reception Centre.

Officials report that public facilities such as schools and health centers are struggling to cope amid limited resources and ongoing donor funding cuts.

#NBSLiveAt1 #NBSUpdates

text:
Speaker of Parliament, Annet Anita Among, has flagged off Uganda’s representatives for the upcoming African Secondary Schools competition set to take place in Ghana next week. 

St. Noah Girls’ School will compete in the girls’ category, while St. Mary’s Kitende will represent Uganda in the boys’ category.

#NBSLiveAt1 #NBSUpdates

text:
The NRM National Treasurer, Hon. Amb. Barbara Nekesa Oundo, yesterday presided over the closure of the five-day Uganda Secondary Schools' Championship for the Bukedi subregion. The competitions took place at Madibira Primary School in Busia Municipality.

The tournament drew participants from 58 schools across the subregion, with Busia Secondary School coming top among the boys and Tororo Girls School emerging victorious from the girls' competitions.

The two champions will be joined by the 1st and 2nd runners-up to represent the subregion at the national level.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/nrm-committed-improving-sports-amb-nekesa

text:
‎‎The NRM leaders from the Acholi west districts have endorsed President and Party National Chairman, H.E Yoweri Kaguta Museveni as the sole candidate for the 2026 elections and beyond, saying he is still very popular and steadfast towards improving the country's prosperity. 

‎‎The leaders who included NRM district Chairpersons, District Executive Committees, sub-county and opinion leaders from Gulu, Omoro, Nwoya and Amuru districts, declared their support for President Museveni's sole candidature today at a meeting that was called by NRM Secretary General, Rt.Hon.Richard Todwong at St Monica Adel Center in Gulu City. 

‎‎The leaders who spoke at length during the meeting said they haven't seen a leader in the NRM who is as popular, visionary and capable as President Museveni. 

‎"We support President Museveni for another term because he has championed the restoration of the existing relative peace, stability, and inclusivity of all people in the growth and development of the country. It is the reason we support his presidential bid without any internal contests," the leaders said.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/news/acholi-nrm-leaders-endorse-president-museveni-sole-candidate-2026-elections

text:
The NRM Secretary General, Rt Hon. Richard Todwong has arrived at St Monica Tailoring Centre in Gulu City where he is expected to address Party leaders, local government officials and technocrats from districts of Acholi West which includes; Gulu, Gulu City, Omoro, Amuru and Nwoya. 

‎The convened meeting is aimed at invigorating them ahead of the NRM primary and general elections.

text: More than 40 years ago, when people were diagnosed with HIV/Aids, they were often given only one to two years to live. As a result, the issues surrounding aging were not a significant focus for those living with the virus #MonitorUpdates

text: QUOTE: “We must be brave and avoid keeping silent about issues that affect our people and our areas. This is the only path that will drive us forward as a kingdom. The leadership that will build a strong kingdom and Uganda as a whole must respect human rights, freedom of worship and culture. Our people must be given a chance to voice out their concerns and be able to shape their destiny.” - Kabaka Mutebi during Local Governments Day celebrations on May 21, 2017 #MonitorUpdates

text:
President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni has expressed gratitude that Uganda is now united and peaceful.

“I'm glad that Uganda is now united and peaceful, and we are able to build national institutions. You have seen that when we are recruiting in the army, we recruit in the whole country on an equal basis. There's a quota for every district,” he said.

The President made the remarks yesterday while officiating at the Peace Day celebrations in Yumbe District.

Read More: https://www.nrm.ug/blog/im-glad-uganda-now-united-and-peaceful-says-president-museveni-during-peace-day-celebrations

His Excellency President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni has arrived at Boma grounds in Yumbe district where he will preside over the West Nile peace day celebrations.

‎The event marks 23 years in the subregion since  the NRM government and the former rebel groups signed a peace agreement to cease fighting.
